  "prompt": "How can I report someone on Quora?",
  "response": "To report someone on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the User's Profile**: Navigate to the profile of the user you want to report.\n\n2. **Click on the Three Dots**: Look for the three dots (ellipsis) typically found near their profile name or bio.\n\n3. **Select \"Report\"**: Click on \"Report\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n4. **Choose the Reason**: You'll be prompted to select a reason for your report. Choose the option that best describes the issue (e.g., harassment, spam, etc.).\n\n5. **Submit Your Report**: After selecting the reason, provide any additional information if required, then submit the report.\n\nQuora takes reports seriously and will review them according to their community guidelines. If you believe a post or comment violates their policies, you can also report that specific content using a similar process.",
